-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 33.01pt; padding-left:2.99pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">I am unable to carry out work in a domestic property due to not being registered to a registered body ie. NAPPIT</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> NICIEC</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> etc</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">. T</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">he alternative is to pay a fee to the local government to send someone out to test</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> and inspect</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> my work who may be less qualified</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> but a kitchen fitter who has</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> in the past</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> attend a Part P course</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">, or</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> now has attended a 4 week Domestic Electrical Insta</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">llation Managed Learning Programme can apply and pay a fee to be registered to an affiliated</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> body</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> which will enabl</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">e him to install and sign</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> off</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> his own work.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> I examine students every week who have done 3-4 years training who still cannot reach the require</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">d industry standards.</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">I fail to see how somebody can be competent in such a short space of time.</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">I see these bodies as money making organisations trying to keep a niche market for themselves. </span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">The solution is have only time-served tradesmen who have a JIB</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">/ECS</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> grading</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> card</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> (which</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> has a photo</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> of person</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> proving identity) </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">which already exists as a body having stamp</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ed</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> on the card what level of competence they are at. The fee </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">(approx</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> £15) for this is far less than what the other organisations are charging. This </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">is done on an individual basis not as a cover for one person in a company signing all employees work off.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">This would simplify the already very complicated and confusing system.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> How was this missed when first thinking about proving competence?</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:right"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">25 November 2013</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="color:#365f91; font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div></body></html>